This product includes software developed as a verified, high-performance Rust
backend for the data-expansion stage of sequential target trial emulation.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Attribution
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This project reproduces, and validates bit-for-bit against, the behaviour of the
R package "TrialEmulation":

    TrialEmulation: An R Package to Emulate Target Trials for Causal Analysis of
    Observational Time-to-event Data.
    Maintainer: Isaac Gravestock (Roche). Authors include Li Su (MRC-BSU),
    Roonak Rezvani, Julia Moesch. Funded by the MRC and Roche.
    Repository: https://github.com/Causal-LDA/TrialEmulation
    License: Apache-2.0

"TrialEmulation" is the Oracle for this project: it is used (unmodified) to
generate validation fixtures. tte-expand is an independent reimplementation of
the deterministic data-expansion stage; it is not a fork of, and is not endorsed
by, the TrialEmulation maintainers unless stated otherwise. Any fixtures derived
from the package's shipped example data are credited to the package.
